The paper discusses software architecture recovery, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE). The use of different methods and tools to recover the architecture suggests a focus on programming languages (cs.PL) and software design (cs.SD). The measurement of results and comparison to expert opinions suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and cryptography (cs.CR).
